1
00:00:21,433 --> 00:00:23,033
Perfect.

2
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:28,533
Time to go.

3
00:00:31,633 --> 00:00:33,167
POLYESTER - SILK - COTTON
MODAL - TRIACETATE

4
00:00:33,233 --> 00:00:34,533
Silk, okay.

5
00:02:15,767 --> 00:02:17,467
ISHIKAWA TAILOR

6
00:02:30,033 --> 00:02:31,033
Mayu!

7
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,967
Yuri.

8
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:37,933
I knew it.
You forgot.

9
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,633
Sorry.

10
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:42,333
We were supposed to have tea before work.

11
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,467
You should have called me.

12
00:02:45,533 --> 00:02:48,233
Well, I hit it off
with a guy sitting next to me.

13
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:50,267
We started talking,
and time flew by.

14
00:02:50,333 --> 00:02:52,400
Friends already?

15
00:02:52,467 --> 00:02:54,767
I'm starting to feel like
I can make it here.

16
00:02:56,500 --> 00:03:01,667
Hey, do I look okay? I had a really
hard time deciding what to wear.

17
00:03:01,733 --> 00:03:04,967
-Do I look weird? Like a hick?
-No.

18
00:03:05,033 --> 00:03:08,900
You look like you've made an effort.
You'll make a good impression.

19
00:03:08,967 --> 00:03:11,800
Can't you just say I look cute?

20
00:03:11,867 --> 00:03:15,500
You know,
we studied textile at college,

21
00:03:15,567 --> 00:03:18,800
and you chose to wear that
on your first day?

22
00:03:18,867 --> 00:03:20,033
What?

23
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:22,533
But it's a suit.

24
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:24,833
Well, whatever.

25
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:27,733
Oh, my office is this way.
Bye.

26
00:03:29,133 --> 00:03:31,267
We're off to a good start
on our new lives!

27
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:33,300
We won't let Tokyo stop us!

28
00:03:33,367 --> 00:03:34,733
I'll e-mail you later.

29
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:55,167
AZUMA INARI SHRINE

30
00:05:01,833 --> 00:05:03,133
Good morning.

31
00:05:05,867 --> 00:05:08,067
-Good morning.
-Morning.

32
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,633
-The new hire?
-Ms. Tokita.

33
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:12,300
Found this place all right?

34
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:15,967
I'm Mayuko Tokita.
Pleased to meet you.

35
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,333
Um, am I late?

36
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:21,200
It's not that.
Just--

37
00:05:21,267 --> 00:05:24,533
Ms. Tokita. You just got here,
but I need to give you a task.

38
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,067
Yes.

39
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:31,167
Could you take this fabric sample
to Sekiguchi in Nippori?

40
00:05:31,233 --> 00:05:33,267
I'll give you the address.
It's a fabric store.

41
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:36,033
Nippori, the fabric district.

42
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:37,967
Sorry for rushing you like this.

43
00:05:38,033 --> 00:05:39,200
-Hime.
-Yes?

44
00:05:39,267 --> 00:05:40,733
-Give her the map.
-Okay.

45
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:44,367
Sorry for the chaos.
We're having a trunk show this weekend.

46
00:05:45,033 --> 00:05:47,767
-Trunk show?
-Unveiling of our new products.

47
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,800
{\an8}We'll put on a show here in the store.

48
00:05:49,867 --> 00:05:51,133
{\an8}2015 FALL-WINTER PRODUCT LAUNCH

49
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:53,833
-Hey, photos of the fitting?
-Yes.

50
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:56,700
Sorry about that.

51
00:05:56,767 --> 00:05:58,667
Isn't this gorgeous?

52
00:05:58,733 --> 00:06:02,267
These walk right in front of you.
Heaven for men.

53
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:03,467
Right?

54
00:06:03,533 --> 00:06:06,633
I look at those strictly
from a professional--

55
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:07,867
You are mumbling.

56
00:06:07,933 --> 00:06:09,800
-Stop fooling around.
-Mizuki's edgy.

57
00:06:09,867 --> 00:06:11,633
It's her debut.

58
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:13,200
Changed your style too, right?

59
00:06:13,267 --> 00:06:15,733
She designs shapes first.
Straight as an arrow.

60
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:18,967
Say what you like.
I'm staking my whole life on this.

61
00:06:20,667 --> 00:06:21,767
Hurry up.

62
00:06:22,733 --> 00:06:24,033
I'm off.

63
00:06:24,100 --> 00:06:25,100
Wait, the map!

64
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:29,167
Design change?
We only have five days.

65
00:06:29,233 --> 00:06:31,333
THESE THREE DESIGNS WILL BE CHANGED
FOR THE APRIL 11 TRUNK SHOW

66
00:06:37,333 --> 00:06:40,533
Ah, the design change,
as expected.

67
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,900
The boss seemed
to be in that kind of mood.

68
00:06:42,967 --> 00:06:45,733
And what's more,
three of them!

69
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,433
Only five days until the show.

70
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:49,600
Well, what's that saying?

71
00:06:49,667 --> 00:06:52,467
Nothing new.
We'll just move on.

72
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:56,733
Fumi, do we have the new designs?

73
00:06:56,800 --> 00:07:01,067
Um...
We have two out of the three.

74
00:07:01,967 --> 00:07:04,500
All these are my design.

75
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:07,333
She came up with something, again.

76
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:11,433
So we'll make these two,
and the last one...

77
00:07:12,133 --> 00:07:13,233
We'll just wait.

78
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:14,433
NEW HIRE
TRUNK SHOW

79
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:16,467
Will she change the staging too?

80
00:07:16,533 --> 00:07:18,333
Talk to the boss.

81
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:20,600
I don't think she'll change that.

82
00:07:20,667 --> 00:07:22,333
We can't postpone it now.

83
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:24,700
We've already sent out the invitation.

84
00:07:24,767 --> 00:07:27,933
We'll go on with the show on the 11th.

85
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,667
That's our schedule.

86
00:07:29,733 --> 00:07:30,733
Okay.

87
00:07:38,667 --> 00:07:41,133
-Give it to me.
-Yes.

88
00:07:41,967 --> 00:07:43,700
I'm sure you'll go through a lot,

89
00:07:44,700 --> 00:07:46,100
but we'll do this together, okay?

90
00:07:48,133 --> 00:07:49,133
Okay.

91
00:07:50,833 --> 00:07:54,167
"Emotion is a made-to-order
lingerie maker.

92
00:07:54,233 --> 00:07:57,200
We take detailed measurements
of our customers,

93
00:07:57,267 --> 00:07:58,967
listen to their requests,

94
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:03,700
and make the one and only lingerie
in the world for each of them.

95
00:08:03,767 --> 00:08:07,733
So, these are just images
that our president Mayumi Nanjo offers.

96
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:09,933
They're not for sale."

97
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,900
Perfect.

98
00:08:11,967 --> 00:08:14,600
I couldn't say it so smoothly.

99
00:08:14,667 --> 00:08:18,467
These are called haute couture, right?

100
00:08:18,533 --> 00:08:21,967
Well, strictly speaking,
they're not.

101
00:08:22,033 --> 00:08:24,100
They're one of a kind.

102
00:08:24,167 --> 00:08:25,733
Lavish, isn't it?

103
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:29,667
It's really amazing,
creating all the way from fabric.

104
00:08:29,733 --> 00:08:31,033
Indeed.

105
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:32,700
What, fabric?

106
00:08:32,767 --> 00:08:36,367
I'm so excited.
I studied textile at college.

107
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:41,700
It's my dream to develop new materials
like microfiber or carbon fiber.

108
00:08:41,767 --> 00:08:45,967
Wait.
We don't develop new fabrics.

109
00:08:46,533 --> 00:08:47,733
Huh?

110
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:51,267
But Ms. Nanjo said we create
from scratch.

111
00:08:52,133 --> 00:08:55,333
I think you have the wrong idea
about our job.

112
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:58,200
You should have a talk with her.

113
00:09:00,300 --> 00:09:02,400
That's her atelier.

114
00:09:12,933 --> 00:09:14,567
This material...

115
00:09:15,967 --> 00:09:18,200
Bare jersey made with rayon
and polyurethane.

116
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:21,900
Stretchable and so sleek.

117
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:23,733
I'm in heaven!

118
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,700
Quite a soliloquist.

119
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:36,833
Ms. Nanjo...
Good morning.

120
00:09:42,467 --> 00:09:43,933
You're cute.

121
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:49,400
I envy young girls.
They don't need any effort to be cute.

122
00:09:49,467 --> 00:09:52,467
Such radiant, firm skin.

123
00:09:52,533 --> 00:09:54,700
What do you eat to keep it?

124
00:09:54,767 --> 00:09:56,233
No, I'm wrong.

125
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:58,467
It doesn't matter what you eat.

126
00:09:58,533 --> 00:10:03,067
You eat salty and greasy food to death,
but it stays smooth.

127
00:10:03,133 --> 00:10:06,933
I'll bet mosquitoes just slide off it.
Nowhere for them to bite.

128
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,833
Just joking.

129
00:10:10,133 --> 00:10:11,700
What's good about that fabric?

130
00:10:13,067 --> 00:10:15,000
That.
Rayon bare jersey.

131
00:10:15,067 --> 00:10:17,200
Oh. Um...

132
00:10:18,133 --> 00:10:21,367
Stretchable,
produces great colors,

133
00:10:21,433 --> 00:10:25,300
and absorbs moisture well,
very functional as underwear.

134
00:10:25,367 --> 00:10:27,467
Very soft texture.

135
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:30,300
Processed to prevent shrinkage,

136
00:10:30,367 --> 00:10:32,167
-so it's washable--
-Bad things?

137
00:10:32,233 --> 00:10:34,767
-It's heavy.
-So knowledgeable.

138
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:39,800
I'm Mayuko Tokita.
Thank you for hiring me.

139
00:10:39,867 --> 00:10:41,333
But...

140
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:43,233
may I ask you a question?

141
00:10:44,367 --> 00:10:48,667
At the interview, I heard I could
develop fabrics that can be used--

142
00:10:48,733 --> 00:10:50,967
But too bad.
You're tacky.

143
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:55,867
You have firm and smooth skin,
you know a lot about fabrics.

144
00:10:55,933 --> 00:10:57,433
But you're tacky.

145
00:10:58,300 --> 00:10:59,733
Grossly tacky.

146
00:11:00,867 --> 00:11:02,667
Stand two meters away from me.

147
00:11:03,933 --> 00:11:05,133
Pardon?

148
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:09,033
Women who don't care about beauty
make me want to punch them.

149
00:11:11,367 --> 00:11:14,167
Okay, okay.
I'll take care of her.

150
00:11:14,233 --> 00:11:16,533
I was going to ask you to run an errand.

151
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:19,400
You're going shopping in Ginza.
It'll be fun!

152
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:25,867
Thank you very much.
Give my regards to Ms. Nanjo.

153
00:11:25,933 --> 00:11:28,467
I hope the show is a success.

154
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:31,433
Thanks.

155
00:11:32,667 --> 00:11:33,733
Wait.

156
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:40,633
I'm a regular customer of Emotion too.

157
00:11:41,733 --> 00:11:44,433
That's...
Thank you very much.

158
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:49,233
Sorry for my outfit.

159
00:11:51,267 --> 00:11:55,333
Please tell Ms. Nanjo I'll let her know
when we get more good stuff.

160
00:11:56,567 --> 00:11:57,767
Okay.

161
00:12:03,433 --> 00:12:06,867
Here's the Raphael Collin's piece
Ms. Nanjo ordered.

162
00:12:09,633 --> 00:12:12,467
Those shoes look comfortable.

163
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:19,100
I'm a working woman.
These shoes are perfect.

164
00:12:19,167 --> 00:12:20,167
Huh?

165
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:23,433
Sorry for being tacky.

166
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:32,167
What's so wrong with this outfit?

167
00:12:33,433 --> 00:12:34,967
I hate this town!

168
00:12:45,133 --> 00:12:48,033
Something like this,
in green this time.

169
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:50,800
I'll gather up torchon laces for you.

170
00:12:51,767 --> 00:12:53,200
7,000 yen...

171
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:58,000
70,000!

172
00:12:58,067 --> 00:12:59,500
{\an8}MRS. MUROI
PURCHASE AMOUNT

173
00:13:08,167 --> 00:13:11,833
-So, the trunk show is this Saturday.
-Yes.

174
00:13:11,900 --> 00:13:16,233
Most brands have already finished
showing their fall-winter collection.

175
00:13:17,233 --> 00:13:20,600
What delayed your show?

176
00:13:21,567 --> 00:13:23,400
Any issues with you, Ms. Nanjo?

177
00:13:24,367 --> 00:13:26,233
No particular reason.

178
00:13:26,300 --> 00:13:28,167
Everyone's wondering.

179
00:13:28,233 --> 00:13:30,633
"What will Mayumi Nanjo create next?"

180
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:33,933
It determines the lingerie trend in Japan.

181
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:39,100
I, for one, keep doing this job
just to see your new creation.

182
00:13:39,167 --> 00:13:41,367
I'm very flattered.

183
00:13:41,433 --> 00:13:43,167
But I'm a little worried.

184
00:13:43,967 --> 00:13:47,633
I can attest to the fact that Emotion's
lingerie is the best of the world,

185
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:52,233
but today your products are
more like traditional craft than fashion.

186
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:55,600
You did not just say that.

187
00:13:56,367 --> 00:13:57,867
You're welcome.

188
00:13:58,867 --> 00:14:03,500
I make the same things again and again?
It's none of your concern.

189
00:14:03,567 --> 00:14:07,267
A critic should not meddle with
a maker's creative process.

190
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:10,800
All you need to do is evaluate
the finished products.

191
00:14:10,867 --> 00:14:14,700
It's always a critic with good eyes
that leads the culture.

192
00:14:14,767 --> 00:14:17,967
Wanna hear more? You're in a rut.
No novelty.

193
00:14:18,033 --> 00:14:20,367
Laces, silk, embroidery, silk again.

194
00:14:20,433 --> 00:14:22,533
Shut up, you noisy hag.

195
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,300
We're two of a kind.

196
00:14:24,367 --> 00:14:28,800
Well, okay, let's stop there.
Please, Shuko--

197
00:14:28,867 --> 00:14:29,933
Quiet, Saru.

198
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:33,167
Listen, I have only one criterion,

199
00:14:33,233 --> 00:14:35,633
and that's whether it's beautiful or not.

200
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:39,267
And what makes it beautiful

201
00:14:39,367 --> 00:14:42,400
is not just design or how it looks.

202
00:14:42,467 --> 00:14:45,433
Top class material,
elaborate patterns,

203
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:47,300
high-quality sewing,

204
00:14:47,367 --> 00:14:49,133
maximum comfort,

205
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:52,233
reasonable prices,
customer satisfaction.

206
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:56,000
Only the products that have all of these
can be called beautiful.

207
00:14:56,067 --> 00:14:59,800
-But--
-Novelty? What's novelty?

208
00:14:59,867 --> 00:15:02,600
No one knows what it will be.

209
00:15:02,667 --> 00:15:04,533
Don't expect us to be new.

210
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:10,300
I have made and will always make
only beautiful products.

211
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:14,333
Big mouth, as always.

212
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:17,633
Okay, let's wrap it up then.

213
00:15:19,133 --> 00:15:21,233
Looking forward to the trunk show.

214
00:15:31,533 --> 00:15:32,600
It's rare

215
00:15:33,533 --> 00:15:35,667
to see you in such distress.

216
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:41,200
I am aware of all the noise around me.

217
00:15:42,133 --> 00:15:47,000
You've been an icon
in the lingerie industry for 30 years.

218
00:15:48,967 --> 00:15:50,167
You wanna quit?

219
00:15:52,167 --> 00:15:54,367
Did I say such a thing?

220
00:16:03,433 --> 00:16:05,033
Organize the stockroom.

221
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:07,067
It's so messy.

222
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:09,500
That's why my head is messy inside too.

223
00:16:19,233 --> 00:16:20,967
These are...

224
00:16:24,433 --> 00:16:28,233
I feel so at home!

225
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:31,100
Straps, adjusters...

226
00:16:31,167 --> 00:16:34,567
Loops go there.
Good, perfect.

227
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:37,067
Such a soliloquist.

228
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:40,333
Tough first day, isn't it?

229
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:43,200
Wish we could give you a welcome party.

230
00:16:43,267 --> 00:16:46,533
It's okay.
I love doing this.

231
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:50,100
Better than a welcome party
or a drinking party.

232
00:16:50,167 --> 00:16:51,600
A hundred times better.

233
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:56,167
You're funny.

234
00:16:56,233 --> 00:17:00,933
Mayuko Tokita. Where did you
go to college? Oh, yeah, Nagano.

235
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:03,100
What are you doing with those?

236
00:17:03,167 --> 00:17:05,600
-Throwing them away.
-Why?

237
00:17:05,667 --> 00:17:06,967
They're very nice.

238
00:17:07,033 --> 00:17:10,100
This silk is among the best.

239
00:17:10,167 --> 00:17:12,233
No matter how good they are,

240
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:14,467
we never put them out
if the boss is dissatisfied.

241
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:16,200
That's our motto.

242
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:23,233
Hello, um...
New girl!

243
00:17:23,300 --> 00:17:25,433
The boss?
Yes!

244
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:27,100
Bring me coffee.

245
00:17:27,167 --> 00:17:28,800
Okay!

246
00:17:28,867 --> 00:17:31,267
-You don't mind that?
-What?

247
00:17:33,167 --> 00:17:34,200
Drink whatever you like.

248
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:37,267
Fits for a fashionable office.

249
00:17:38,467 --> 00:17:40,667
It's not so rare though.

250
00:17:41,767 --> 00:17:44,867
Fumi, has the boss
given you the new design?

251
00:17:44,933 --> 00:17:49,033
Not yet.
She's never been this late before.

252
00:17:49,100 --> 00:17:50,533
Right.

253
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:56,233
She must be so shocked.

254
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:02,933
This trunk show was the first time
her design was chosen.

255
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:06,133
Three of them.
But then...

256
00:18:07,533 --> 00:18:08,633
That thing this morning?

257
00:18:09,667 --> 00:18:13,200
Samples had already been made,
but all of them were scrapped.

258
00:18:14,267 --> 00:18:17,300
The ones Mr. Saruhashi threw away...

259
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:21,367
You're bringing coffee to the boss, right?

